

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="self"
  description="self index / identity, play, paradox, wanderer, and becoming"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-kicker">self / archive wing / index</div>
    <h1>self</h1>
    <p>
      identity, play, paradox, wandering, and the shifting center that moves
      through every other part of the archive. the self is not a fixed thing,
      but a living relation between what is known, unknown, chosen, and becoming.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      this wing gathers pages on personality, imagination, contradiction,
      seeking, and the ongoing work of becoming more fully real.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">entry sequence</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <div class="grid-links">
        <a href="/self/identity">
          <span class="link-title">identity</span>
          <span class="link-desc">self-concept, roles, memory, and the sense of "I".</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/self/intuition">
          <span class="link-title">intuition</span>
          <span class="link-desc">inner knowing, pattern recognition, and non-linear understanding.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/self/play">
          <span class="link-title">play</span>
          <span class="link-desc">freedom, experimentation, improvisation, and living movement.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/self/paradox">
          <span class="link-title">paradox</span>
          <span class="link-desc">contradiction, tension, doubleness, and incompatible truths.</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/self/wanderer">
          <span class="link-title">wanderer</span>
          <span class="link-desc">seeking, exile, distance, movement, and the path without certainty.</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">how to read</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p>
        this section is more central than it first appears. every other wing of
        the archive returns here in some form, because every symbol, dream,
        transformation, or vision is also an event in the life of the self.
      </p>
      <p>
        read this wing as a movement rather than a doctrine. identity becomes
        more real through tension, play, contradiction, and searching—not by
        staying fixed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">self map</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p><a href="/self/identity" class="link-blue">identity</a> — self-concept, memory, and structure of self</p>
      <p><a href="/self/intuition" class="link-red">intuition</a> — inner knowing, pattern, non-linear sense</p>
      <p><a href="/self/play" class="link-red">play</a> — freedom, experiment, improvisation</p>
      <p><a href="/self/paradox" class="link-green">paradox</a> — contradiction, tension, doubleness</p>
      <p><a href="/self/wanderer">wanderer</a> — seeking, exile, movement, path</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <div class="box-title">note</div>
    <div class="box-body">
      <p class="muted">
        this wing is arranged as a circular path: identity → intuition → play → paradox
        → wanderer → back to identity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>